whence <bibl n="PHI"><author>McCabe</author> <title level="m">PHI Aphrodisias</title> <biblScope n="257572">685</biblScope></bibl>. Cormack suggests that there were two
identical inscriptions, whence <bibl type="hbi" n="cormack1964">, <title level="m">ABSA</title> 59, <date value="1964" notBefore="1964" notAfter="1964" exact="both">1964</date>, no. <biblScope>23.2</biblScope></bibl>,  <bibl n="PHI"><author>McCabe</author> <title level="m">PHI Aphrodisias</title> <biblScope n="257573">686</biblScope></bibl>; this may have been a reference to  <xref type="inscription" n="204" href="040017">4.17</xref>, which is not identical.</p>
      </div>

